def _get_grouper(
    obj,
    key=None,
    axis=0,
    level=None,
    sort=True,
    observed=False,
    mutated=False,
    validate=True,
):
    """
    Fixed version of _get_grouper function.
    """
    if axis == 1:
        # when grouping along the columns, use column names as keys
        keys = obj.columns if key is None else key
        groupings = []
        group_axis = obj._get_axis(1)
        for key in keys:
            ping = Grouping(
                group_axis,
                obj[key],
                obj=obj,
                name=key,
                level=level,
                sort=sort,
                observed=observed,
                in_axis=True,
            )
            groupings.append(ping)

        if len(groupings) == 0 and len(obj.columns):
            raise ValueError("No group keys passed!")

        grouper = BaseGrouper(group_axis, groupings, sort=sort, mutated=mutated)
        return grouper, [], obj

    else:
        # handle grouping along the index (axis=0) as before
        group_axis = obj._get_axis(0)
